{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.23",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 23,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 23",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 23 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.23.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:1",
      "text": "Then Job answered,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.23.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:2",
      "text": "“ Even today my complaint is rebellious. His hand is heavy in spite of my groaning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.23.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:3",
      "text": "Oh that I knew where I might find him! That I might come even to his seat!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.23.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:4",
      "text": "I would set my cause in order before him, and fill my mouth with arguments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.23.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:5",
      "text": "I would know the words which he would answer me, and understand what he would tell me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.23.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:6",
      "text": "Would he contend with me in the greatness of his power? No, but he would listen to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.23.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:7",
      "text": "There the upright might reason with him, so I should be delivered forever from my judge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.23.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:8",
      "text": "“ If I go east, he is not there. If I go west, I can ’t find him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.23.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:9",
      "text": "He works to the north, but I can ’t see him. He turns south, but I can ’t catch a glimpse of him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.23.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:10",
      "text": "But he knows the way that I take. When he has tried me, I will come out like gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.23.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:11",
      "text": "My foot has held fast to his steps. I have kept his way, and not turned away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.23.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:12",
      "text": "I haven’t gone back from the commandment of his lips. I have treasured up the words of his mouth more than my necessary food.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.23.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:13",
      "text": "But he stands alone, and who can oppose him? What his soul desires, even that he does.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.23.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:14",
      "text": "For he performs that which is appointed for me. Many such things are with him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.23.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:15",
      "text": "Therefore I am terrified at his presence. When I consider, I am afraid of him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.23.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:16",
      "text": "For God has made my heart faint. The Almighty has terrified me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.23.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:17",
      "text": "Because I was not cut off before the darkness, neither did he cover the thick darkness from my face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
